# ─── AI Connector (ContentOS) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Both variables below are OPTIONAL. Leaving them unset (or empty) keeps the
# deterministic content generator active — createContentGenerator() only ever
# attempts the AI path when useAI is requested AND isConnectorConfigured()
# is true. AI generation is NOT enabled merely by the presence of this file.
#
# Model note: the Supabase edge function this connector calls currently
# specifies a model identifier. Its validity is NOT verified or endorsed
# here — model verification is a separate, unresolved follow-up item.

# Optional. Authenticates the frontend's request to the AI connector's
# Supabase edge function via the `x-api-key` header.
#
# IMPORTANT: because this variable uses the VITE_ prefix, Vite bundles its
# value into client-side JavaScript — it is visible to anyone inspecting the
# built app. Do NOT treat it as a confidential server-side secret. It only
# identifies "this request came from our frontend"; it is not a substitute
# for a real user credential. The actual OpenAI API key stays server-side
# only, in the Supabase function's own secrets, and is never sent to the
# browser.
#
# Never commit a real value here.
VITE_API_KEY=

# Optional override for the AI connector's Supabase function endpoint.
# Leaving this empty uses the connector's built-in default endpoint.
#
# If set, this MUST be a trusted HTTPS Supabase function URL. Configuring
# an arbitrary origin here would send the frontend connector key (if set)
# and the generation request payload to that origin.
#
# Never commit a real deployment-specific value here.
VITE_SUPABASE_FUNCTION_URL=
